data.name: Classic American Cheeseburger with Sweet Potato Fries
data.quickTastyDescription: A juicy beef patty topped with melted cheddar, crisp lettuce, and ripe tomato, served with crispy sweet potato fries.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C) for the sweet potato fries.
Cut the sweet potatoes into thin wedges and toss them in olive oil, salt, pepper, and paprika.
Spread the sweet potatoes on a baking sheet in a single layer and bake for 25 minutes, turning halfway through.
While the fries are baking, form the ground beef into 4 patties, season with salt and pepper.

Heat a grill pan or outdoor grill over medium-high heat, and cook the patties for about 4-5 minutes on each side for medium doneness, adding a slice of cheddar cheese on top during the last minute of cooking to melt.
Toast the hamburger buns on the grill for 1-2 minutes until golden brown.
Assemble the burgers by placing the lettuce, cooked patty with cheese, and tomato on each bun, and top with the other half of the bun.
Serve the cheeseburgers hot with a side of sweet potato fries.
